article.description: JaQuail Townser scored 17 points, Andre Statam added 16 and Jacksonville State beat Oakwood University 96-60 on Monday night.
article.headline: Jacksonville State downs Oakwood 96-60
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- JaQuail Townser scored 17 points, Andre Statam added 16 and Jacksonville State beat Oakwood University 96-60 on Monday night. Christian Cunningham and Jared Hamilton scored 12 apiece for the Gamecocks (2-1), who outrebounded their United States Collegiate Athletic Association opponent 46-38. Malcom Drumwright added 11 points with nine of the 24 assists Jacksonville State used in making 39 of 76 field goals (51 percent). Townser, who shot 4 of 5 from beyond the arc, opened the game with a 3-pointer and ended the first half with a turnaround jumper in the closing seconds for a 53-32 halftime lead. Cunningham scored two dunks in the first four and a half minutes and the Gamecocks scored 54 points in the paint and 14 points off of seven Ambassadors turnovers. Ronnie Abrams led Oakwood (4-7) with 13 points and Ollie Felps added 12.
